HEADWORD: Empeople
<hw>Em*peo"ple</hw> <pr>(⟦ecr⟧m*p⟦emac⟧"p'l)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos>
<def>To form into a people or community; to inhabit; to people.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>We now know 't is very well <qex>empeopled</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Sir
T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

